<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro LFS_UNLOCK(cfg) is defined as ((void)cfg). In lfs_dir_open the call LFS_UNLOCK(lfs->cfg) is executed but performs no action (and the expression lfs->cfg has no side-effects). Removing that call would not change program behaviour in this build, so it constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (Note: if the macro is conditionally defined in other builds to perform a real unlock or if cfg has side-effects, then it would not be dead in those builds.)
